Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.00,0:01:23.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,[历史频道] 第二季 第二集 宇宙中的洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}[History Channel] The UniverseⅡ 02of19 Cosmic.Holes
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.36,0:01:28.79,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,宇宙是一个一切皆有可能的聚宝盆\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The universe is a cosmic cornucopia of endless possibilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.04,0:01:32.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,设想穿梭往返到宇宙中的任何一个地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Imagine a shuttle service to anywhere in the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.92,0:01:37.41,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不是登上未来的宇宙飞船\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's not aboard a futuristic spaceship;
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.91,0:01:40.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,而是乘坐银河交通工具通过虫洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's a galactic ride through a wormhole...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.84,0:01:42.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一种理论上的通道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a theoretical tunnel.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.56,0:01:45.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,提供了通过时空的捷径\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}providing shortcuts through space and time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.75,0:01:51.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,虫洞有点象城市中的地铁系统\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Wormholes are a little bit like a subway system that you might use in the city
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.19,0:01:53.88,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你进入一个洞口\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where you're going into a hole
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.00,0:01:56.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,经过一个隧道然后在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you go through a tunnel and then you come out
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.32,0:01:58.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,另外一头的洞口出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at the other end through another hole
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.54,0:02:02.18,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这样你就穿越了城市 同样也可能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then you've traveled through the city. Same thing would be possible
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.30,0:02:06.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,通过虫洞在宇宙间两个不同地点之间进行旅行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in a wormhole to travel between different points in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.61,0:02:10.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,物理学家克利福德·约翰逊\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Physicist Clifford Johnson
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.45,0:02:13.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,已经对虫洞的可能性进行过深思\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has contemplated the possibility of wormholes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.10,0:02:22.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,虫洞与地铁之间的区别\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The difference between a wormhole and a subway system
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.39,0:02:24.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在于你通过虫洞旅行的行程\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is that you're using the wormhole
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.51,0:02:27.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,要比你在平常的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to travel a greater distance than you would
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.68,0:02:31.79,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,空间里旅行大得多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if you were traveling in ordinary space.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.43,0:02:36.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,理论上虫洞是连接出入口的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In theory a wormhole has a throat
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.35,0:02:39.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,咽喉称做"嘴巴"\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}connected to an entrance and exit called "mouths"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.97,0:02:42.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,嘴巴位于空间的各个部位\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}located in different parts of space.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.64,0:02:46.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,虫洞很有吸引力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A wormhole is appealing because
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.78,0:02:50.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为我们受光速的限制无法超过光速到达仙女星座\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we're limited by the speed of light. We can't get to the Andromeda galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.74,0:02:56.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,即使达到光速也需要60万年才能到达\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in less than something like 600,000 years even moving at the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.58,0:02:59.45,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我一直感到疑惑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I keep wondering if
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.57,0:03:03.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,天文学的下一个伟大的发现究竟是不是虫洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the really next big discovery in astronomy could be a wormhole.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.20,0:03:07.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,现在只是因为它们引起了象我这样的人的兴趣\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Not just because they're fun for people like me
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.80,0:03:10.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,而不是因为\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but because
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.26,0:03:14.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们可以将我们带到某些我们貌似无法用其他途径抵达的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they could take us to some place that we can't plausibly ever get any other way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.02,0:03:21.51,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,格里高里·本福德已经在构思外层空间的科幻小说了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Gregory Benford has pondered the science and fiction of outer space.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.11,0:03:26.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,身兼物理学家和30多部科幻小说的作家\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As both a physicist and author of over 30 sci-fi novels
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.15,0:03:31.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,本福德已经目睹了科幻成真\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Benford has witnessed fantastical theories become a reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.88,0:03:34.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们中许多人都想知道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A lot of us would like to know if wormholes
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.99,0:03:38.73,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,虫洞是真的存在？或者只是建立在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}really exist or whether they're just another mathematical construct
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.85,0:03:41.09,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,爱因斯坦天赋上的又一个数学模型呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}thought up by Einstein the genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.98,0:03:45.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,爱因斯坦的广义相对论\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Albert Einstein's general relativity laws
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.97,0:03:48.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,考虑到了虫洞的存在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}allows for the existence of wormholes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.95,0:03:53.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,1930年爱因斯坦和他的同事纳森·罗森\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In 1930 Einstein and his colleague Nathan Rosen
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.32,0:03:57.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,计算出了这些星系间管道中的一个数学模型\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}calculated the mathematics of one of these intergalactic pipelines.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.26,0:04:01.73,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,也就是大家熟知的"爱因斯坦—罗森桥"\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It became known as the "Einstein-Rosen bridge."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.78,0:04:06.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,虫洞是爱因斯坦方程式的一个解答\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The wormhole is a solution of Einstein's equations for
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.49,0:04:08.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这是广义相对论论述引力作用的方程式\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}general relativity telling us how gravity works.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.93,0:04:10.14,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他们假设\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're hypothetical
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.40,0:04:14.14,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他们这样做是为了将时空的各个部分连接起来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and what they do is they connect different parts of space and time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.42,0:04:18.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,爱因斯坦—罗森的数学虫洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Einstein-Rosen mathematical wormhole
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.64,0:04:21.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是受黑洞的研究启发的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}arose from studying black holes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.81,0:04:28.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,黑洞是引力极其强烈的空间中的一个区域\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A black hole is a region in space of extremely strong gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.31,0:04:30.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,引力强烈到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The gravity is so strong
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.92,0:04:33.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它附近的物体没有任何办法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that there is no way for objects that get too near
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.67,0:04:36.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,挣脱它的引力束缚\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to break away from its gravitational pull.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.70,0:04:40.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,任何东西一旦遭遇到黑洞都无法逃逸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Nothing can escape a close encounter with a black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.35,0:04:41.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,甚至光也同样逃不出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}not even light.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.20,0:04:46.86,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这个倒置的喷泉是个视觉模型\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This inverted fountain serves as a visual analogy
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.98,0:04:48.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,来看一下围绕着黑洞究竟发生了什么\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to what's going on around a black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.84,0:04:52.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在这个黑洞的范围内的底部\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At the bottom is the area inside the event horizon
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.32,0:04:55.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不停地流进去的水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the water falling into it
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.24,0:04:58.45,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,类似于可能流进黑洞的气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is analogous to gas that might fall into a black hole;
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.57,0:05:02.04,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你把自己想象成一条在里面游泳的鱼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Imagine yourself being a fish swimming around this region.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.16,0:05:04.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一旦你掉进这中央\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Once you get down inside this central portion
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.50,0:05:06.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你就此消失在这里而无法返回了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you're past the point of no return.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.17,0:05:11.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是爱因斯坦从未打算将虫洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But Einstein never intended his wormhole
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.94,0:05:13.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,作为太空旅行的工具\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as a tool for space travel.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.85,0:05:20.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他的虫洞只是在某个时间瞬间所创造的理论\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}His wormhole is theoretically created at some moment of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.99,0:05:22.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它短暂打开\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It opens up briefly
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.32,0:05:24.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然后就掐断\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then pinches off.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.25,0:05:28.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,任何企图通过的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Anything that tries to pass through it
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.28,0:05:31.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,都将在它的挤压下粉身碎骨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will get crushed when it squeezes apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.16,0:05:37.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在你的方程式和研究中所记录到的典型的虫洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A typical wormhole that you write down
